13
Subtitle
14
15 TO AMEND THE PEST CONTROL LAW; AND TO
16 REASSIGN CERTAIN DUTIES OF THE STATE
17 PLANT BOARD.
18
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
20
21 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code § 17-37-102(5), concerning definitions
22 pertaining to pest control, is repealed.
23 (5) “Director” means the Director of the State Plant Board;
24
25 SECTION 2. Arkansas Code § 17-37-102(10), concerning definitions
26 pertaining to pest control, is amended to read as follows:
27 (10) “Licensed operator” means a person who has fully qualified
28 and has passed the board's written examination and has in force a valid
29 license from the board Department of Agriculture to engage in the work
30 indicated in the license. The person shall also have met the requirements of
31 and be eligible for certification under the Federal Insecticide, Fungicide,
32 and Rodenticide Act and state law as a commercial applicator;
33
34 SECTION 3. Arkansas Code § 17-37-102(16), concerning definitions
35 pertaining to pest control, is amended to read as follows:
36 (16) “Solicitor” means any person registered with the board
