3 SECTION 13. Arkansas Code § 17-37-215(b), concerning pest control
4 operator names, is amended to read as follows:
5 (b) No person shall issue a solicitor's or agent's license to any
6 other person for the purpose of operating under any other name except that of
7 the licensed operator who registers the solicitor or agent with the State
8 Plant Board Department of Agriculture.
9
10 SECTION 14. Arkansas Code § 17-37-217 is amended to read as follows:
11 17-37-217. Grounds for license invalidation or nonrenewal.
12 Acts which shall be grounds for invalidation or nonrenewal of a license
13 shall include, but shall not be limited to, the following:
14 (1) Misrepresentations for the purpose of deceiving or
15 defrauding;
16 (2) Making of a false statement with knowledge of its falsity
17 for the purpose of inducing others to act thereon to their damage;
18 (3) Failure of the licensee to supply the State Plant Board
19 Department of Agriculture or its authorized representative, upon request,
20 with true and accurate information concerning methods and materials used or
21 work performed or other information essential to the administration and
22 enforcement of this chapter;
23 (4) Performing work, whether for compensation or not, in a
24 classification for which the licensee does not have a license;
25 (5) If repeated inspections by the board department reveal that
26 the licensee is not securing satisfactory control of the pests or diseases
27 which the licensee engages to control or eradicate;
28 (6) Failure of the licensee to register agents or solicitors,
29 failure to pay registration, inspection, or reporting fees due, or failure to
30 make reports within the time specified;
31 (7) Conviction in any court of a violation of this chapter or of
32 the Federal Insecticide, Fungicide, and Rodenticide Act;
33 (8) Intentional misrepresentation in any application for a
34 license;
35 (9) Failure to correct substandard work;
36 (10) Making a pesticide recommendation or application which is
7 02/18/2025 9:24:51 AM LGL066

SB250
1 inconsistent with any or all of the following:
2 (A) The labeling;
3 (B) Federal or state registration; or
4 (C) Federal or state restrictions on the use of that
5 pesticide; and
6 (11) Falsification of records or failure to maintain or make
7 available the records required by this chapter.
8
9 SECTION 15. Arkansas Code § 17-37-221(c), concerning contracts,
10 reports, and records for licensed operators related to pest control, is
11 amended to read as follows:
12 (c)(1)(A) By the fifteenth of each month, every licensed operator
13 shall file a report with the board Department of Agriculture covering termite
14 and other structural pest work performed the previous calendar month.
15 (B) The report required under subdivision (c)(1)(A) of
16 this section shall include:
17 (i) A summary listing of each contract issued for
18 the prevention, control, or eradication of termites or other structural
19 pests;
20 (ii) Letters of clearance issued and service
21 contracts issued regardless of whether chemical treatments were carried out;
22 (iii) The name and address of the property owner;
23 (iv) The address of the property; and
24 (v) Any other information deemed necessary by the
25 board department and stipulated in the rules adopted under this chapter.
26 (C) Within forty-eight (48) normal business hours, the
27 licensed operator shall produce documents requested by an authorized agent of
28 the board department, including without limitation contracts and related
29 documents.
30 (D) Failure to meet timelines set in this section may
31 result in additional penalties.
32 (2)(A) Reporting and payment of inspection fees may also be
33 required for household pest and rodent control work or other classifications
34 as the board department may specify if deemed necessary or if required by the
35 Federal Insecticide, Fungicide, and Rodenticide Act.
36 (B)(i) All fees due the board department shall be filed
